---
// CliRuntimeStackDiagram — the primary architecture diagram for the
// cli-runtime-reframe deck (org#21). Five layers, top to bottom:
//
//   Agent harness (optional) ─┐
//   Human · shell script · CI ─┴─> Robot CLI — control plane
//                                        │  (direct, one-shot ops)
//                                        ▼           ╲
//                              Behavior runtime        ╲
//                                        │               ▼
//                                        ▼        Device daemon /
//                              Device daemon / <────  hardware adapter
//                              hardware adapter
//                                        ↕
//                                Physical robot
//
// Every box and arrow label is taken verbatim from org#21's proposed
// mermaid diagram and terminology table:
//
//   AGENT --> CLI ; HUMAN --> CLI
//   CLI -->|"lifecycle · configuration · direct operations"| RUNTIME
//   CLI -->|"one-shot device operations"| DEVICE   (required direct path)
//   RUNTIME -->|"validated and arbitrated actions"| DEVICE
//   DEVICE <-->|"state and actuation"| ROBOT
//   RUNTIME -.->|"runtime event feed"| AGENT
//   AGENT -.->|"named intents through attach/spool"| RUNTIME
//
// The agent and the physical robot are drawn replaceable (dashed border,
// "optional" / "replaceable" labels) — the architecture accepts any
// intelligence and any body. The CLI and the behavior runtime carry the
// visual emphasis: they are the stable center of the story. "reachy-mini-
// daemon" is named only on the device layer, never on the runtime — the
// behavior runtime and the lower-level device daemon are never conflated.
// Any tick-rate label reads "50 Hz design rate", never a measured claim
// (reachy-mini-cli CHANGELOG v0.42.0 records 23 Hz achieved so far).
//
// Pure inline SVG, no script, no external asset. Theming rides the same
// CSS custom properties as MindNervousSystemBodyDiagram.astro / ReachyDiagram
// (--surface, --line, --ink, --ink-soft, --accent, --accent-strong,
// --font-mono, --font-display, --radius from src/styles/global.css), so
// both dawn themes stay legible. role="img" + aria-labelledby point at a
// <title>/<desc> pair that narrates every layer and every arrow for a
// screen reader. viewBox-based sizing keeps the diagram legible whether
// it renders small inline or full-bleed on a 1920x1080 projected slide.
---

<figure class="cli-runtime-diagram">
  <div class="diagram-viewport">
    <svg
      viewBox="0 0 1200 1100"
      fill="none"
      role="img"
      aria-labelledby="cli-runtime-diagram-title cli-runtime-diagram-desc"
    >
      <title id="cli-runtime-diagram-title">
        A CLI for intelligence, a runtime for embodiment: the five-layer robot architecture
      </title>
      <desc id="cli-runtime-diagram-desc">
        Five layers, drawn top to bottom. At the top, two replaceable entry points feed the
        same control plane: an optional agent harness — Claude Code, Codex, Colleague, a
        custom agent, or none, drawn with a dashed border — and a human, shell script, or CI
        system. Both connect straight down into the robot CLI, the control plane, which
        inspects, configures, intervenes, and reports start, stop, and status through JSON
        contracts; the CLI and the layer below it, the behavior runtime, carry the strongest
        visual weight in this diagram. The CLI sends lifecycle, configuration, and direct
        operations down into the behavior runtime, a continuous fixed-rate loop — 50 Hz is a
        design rate, not a measured one — that runs senses, rules, intents, and arbitration.
        The CLI also has a direct, required path straight down to the device layer, for
        one-shot device operations that bypass the runtime entirely. The behavior runtime
        sends validated, arbitrated actions down to the device daemon or hardware adapter,
        which exchanges state and actuation with the physical robot at the bottom — Reachy
        Mini, SO-ARM101, or a future body, drawn replaceable like the agent above it. Two
        dotted paths connect the agent and the runtime directly, bypassing the CLI: the
        runtime emits a runtime event feed up to the agent, and the agent submits named
        intents back down to the runtime through attach and spool.
      </desc>

      <defs>
        <marker
          id="cli-runtime-arrow-solid"
          viewBox="0 0 10 10"
          refX="8"
          refY="5"
          markerWidth="8"
          markerHeight="8"
          orient="auto-start-reverse"
        >
          <path d="M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 Z" class="arrow-head solid-head"></path>
        </marker>
        <marker
          id="cli-runtime-arrow-dotted"
          viewBox="0 0 10 10"
          refX="8"
          refY="5"
          markerWidth="7"
          markerHeight="7"
          orient="auto-start-reverse"
        >
          <path d="M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 Z" class="arrow-head dotted-head"></path>
        </marker>
      </defs>

      <!-- ============ top row: two replaceable entry points ============ -->

      <g aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="120" y="20" width="470" height="150" rx="20" class="layer-box replaceable"></rect>
        <text x="355" y="52" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker">OPTIONAL — REPLACEABLE</text>
        <text x="355" y="88" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title">Agent harness</text>
        <text x="355" y="114" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">Claude Code · Codex · Colleague</text>
        <text x="355" y="134" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">custom agent · none</text>

        <rect x="610" y="20" width="470" height="150" rx="20" class="layer-box"></rect>
        <text x="845" y="52" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker">DIRECT OPERATOR</text>
        <text x="845" y="90" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title">Human · shell script · CI</text>
        <text x="845" y="118" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">operates the same CLI surface</text>
        <text x="845" y="138" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">no agent required</text>
      </g>

      <!-- AGENT --> CLI ; HUMAN --> CLI -->
      <path d="M355 170 L355 220" class="connector solid" marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"></path>
      <path d="M845 170 L845 220" class="connector solid" marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"></path>

      <!-- ============ Robot CLI — control plane (EMPHASIZED) ============ -->

      <g aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="120" y="220" width="960" height="160" rx="24" class="layer-box emphasis"></rect>
        <text x="600" y="254" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker kicker-strong">CONTROL PLANE</text>
        <text x="600" y="296" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title layer-title-lg">Robot CLI</text>
        <text x="600" y="326" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub layer-sub-lg">
          inspect · configure · intervene
        </text>
        <text x="600" y="350" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub layer-sub-lg">
          start / stop / status · JSON contracts
        </text>
      </g>

      <!-- CLI -->|"lifecycle · configuration · direct operations"| RUNTIME -->
      <path d="M355 380 L355 470" class="connector solid emphasis" marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"></path>
      <text x="600" y="422" text-anchor="middle" class="connector-label">
        lifecycle · configuration · direct operations
      </text>

      <!-- CLI -->|"one-shot device operations"| DEVICE — required direct-intervention path -->
      <path
        d="M1080 300 H1140 V805 H1080"
        class="connector solid bypass required"
        marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"
      ></path>
      <text
        x="1170"
        y="552"
        text-anchor="middle"
        class="connector-label connector-label-required"
        transform="rotate(-90 1170 552)"
      >
        one-shot device operations
      </text>

      <!-- ============ Behavior runtime (EMPHASIZED) ============ -->

      <g aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="120" y="470" width="960" height="190" rx="24" class="layer-box emphasis"></rect>
        <text x="600" y="506" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker kicker-strong">PERSISTENT EMBODIMENT</text>
        <text x="600" y="550" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title layer-title-lg">Behavior runtime</text>
        <text x="600" y="582" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub layer-sub-lg">
          continuous fixed-rate loop — 50 Hz design rate
        </text>
        <text x="600" y="604" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub layer-sub-lg">
          senses · rules · intents · arbitration
        </text>
        <text x="600" y="626" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-note">
          stays alive with no agent attached
        </text>
      </g>

      <!-- RUNTIME -->|"validated and arbitrated actions"| DEVICE -->
      <path d="M355 660 L355 740" class="connector solid emphasis" marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"></path>
      <text x="600" y="704" text-anchor="middle" class="connector-label">validated, arbitrated actions</text>

      <!-- ============ Device daemon / hardware adapter ============ -->

      <g aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="120" y="740" width="960" height="130" rx="20" class="layer-box"></rect>
        <text x="600" y="772" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker">HARDWARE ADAPTER</text>
        <text x="600" y="808" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title">
          Device daemon / hardware adapter
        </text>
        <text x="600" y="836" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">
          reachy-mini-daemon + SDK/HTTP · or the Feetech serial bus
        </text>
      </g>

      <!-- DEVICE <-->|"state and actuation"| ROBOT -->
      <path
        d="M355 870 L355 940"
        class="connector solid"
        marker-start="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"
        marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-solid)"
      ></path>
      <text x="600" y="908" text-anchor="middle" class="connector-label">state and actuation</text>

      <!-- ============ Physical robot — replaceable body ============ -->

      <g aria-hidden="true">
        <rect x="120" y="940" width="960" height="140" rx="20" class="layer-box replaceable"></rect>
        <text x="600" y="974" text-anchor="middle" class="kicker">REPLACEABLE</text>
        <text x="600" y="1012" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-title">Physical robot</text>
        <text x="600" y="1042" text-anchor="middle" class="layer-sub">
          Reachy Mini · SO-ARM101 · future bodies
        </text>
      </g>

      <!-- ============ dotted agent <-> runtime paths, bypassing the CLI ============ -->

      <!-- RUNTIME -.->|"runtime event feed"| AGENT -->
      <path
        d="M120 500 H70 V150 H120"
        class="connector dotted"
        marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-dotted)"
      ></path>
      <text
        x="95"
        y="325"
        text-anchor="middle"
        class="connector-label connector-label-dotted"
        transform="rotate(-90 95 325)"
      >
        runtime event feed
      </text>

      <!-- AGENT -.->|"named intents through attach/spool"| RUNTIME -->
      <path
        d="M120 45 H30 V630 H120"
        class="connector dotted"
        marker-end="url(#cli-runtime-arrow-dotted)"
      ></path>
      <text
        x="55"
        y="337"
        text-anchor="middle"
        class="connector-label connector-label-dotted"
        transform="rotate(-90 55 337)"
      >
        named intents via attach/spool
      </text>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="diagram-caption">
    Solid lines are direct, synchronous calls; the CLI's direct line to the device layer is a
    required one-shot path that bypasses the runtime. Dotted lines are the optional runtime
    event feed and named-intent path an attached agent can use instead.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .cli-runtime-diagram {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .diagram-viewport {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    scrollbar-color: var(--line) transparent;
  }

  .diagram-viewport svg {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 42rem;
    height: auto;
  }

  text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* ---------- layer boxes ---------- */

  .layer-box {
    fill: color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 80%, transparent);
    stroke: var(--line);
    stroke-width: 1.6;
  }

  .layer-box.replaceable {
    stroke-dasharray: 9 7;
  }

  .layer-box.emphasis {
    fill: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 10%, var(--surface));
    stroke: var(--accent-strong);
    stroke-width: 2.6;
  }

  /* ---------- text ---------- */

  .kicker {
    fill: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.09em;
  }

  .kicker-strong {
    fill: var(--accent-strong);
  }

  .layer-title {
    fill: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 27px;
    font-weight: 560;
  }

  .layer-title-lg {
    fill: var(--accent-strong);
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 620;
  }

  .layer-sub {
    fill: var(--ink);
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .layer-sub-lg {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 560;
  }

  .layer-note {
    fill: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  /* ---------- connectors ---------- */

  .connector {
    fill: none;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
  }

  .connector.solid {
    stroke: var(--accent-strong);
    stroke-width: 2.4;
  }

  .connector.solid.emphasis {
    stroke-width: 3;
  }

  .connector.dotted {
    stroke: var(--ink-soft);
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-dasharray: 2 7;
  }

  .arrow-head.solid-head {
    fill: var(--accent-strong);
  }

  .arrow-head.dotted-head {
    fill: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .connector-label {
    fill: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .connector-label-required {
    fill: var(--accent-strong);
    font-weight: 650;
  }

  .connector-label-dotted {
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .diagram-caption {
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .diagram-caption {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
    }
  }
</style>
